item.title: CVE-2023-7084|2024-08-02T08:50:07.797Z -- unknown -- voting%20record
item.description: The Voting Record WordPress plugin through 2.0 is missing sanitisation as well as escaping, which could allow any authenticated users, such as subscriber to perform Stored XSS attacks

item.title: CVE-2023-7083|2024-08-02T08:50:07.903Z -- unknown -- voting%20record
item.description: The Voting Record WordPress plugin through 2.0 does not have CSRF check in some places, and is missing sanitisation as well as escaping, which could allow attackers to make logged in admin add Stored XSS payloads via a CSRF attack
